title: Faulkner Roundup: Hendrix stays perfect in SAA volleyball
text:
Faulkner Roundup: Hendrix stays perfect in SAA volleyball Posted: October 15, 2015 - 6:57pm LOG CABIN DEMOCRAT 
The 24th-ranked Hendrix College volleyball team swept Rhodes College, 25-16, 26-24, 25-16, Wednesday at Grove Gymnasium to move to 10-0 in Southern Athletic Association play.= 
The first place Warriors, who are 16-6 overall, need two more conference wins to secure a share of the regular-season title and the right to host the 2015 SAA Championship Tournament. 
For the match, the Warriors hit .287 with 45 kills, nine aces, 46 digs and five blocks. The Lynx (9-13, 2-8) hit .067 with 22 kills, 10 aces, 35 digs and six blocks. 
Senior libero Felicia Beeman served up a career-high six aces to go with 10 digs. Sophomore right side hitter Lauren Petrisin hit .450, her best of the season, with 12 kills and a pair of blocks. CBC GOLF 
HENDERSON, Tenn. — Central Baptist College’s men’s golf team finished third out of nine teams at the Freed-Hardeman Invitational that ended Tuesday. 
The Mustangs fired a two-day total 611. Columbia College (607) came in first, with Lindenwood University –Belleville (608) second. 
CBC’s Luke Cornett (148) finished third. Other Mustang finishes were: Austin Harmon (6th, 150), Joel Futrell (T18, 157), Cameron Ressor (T21, 159) and Tyler Pinney (T32, 163). CBC VOLLEYBALL 
COLUMBIA, Mo. — Stephens College defeated the Central Baptist College volleyball team (6-21, 0-8), 25-16, 25-11, 25-15, Wednesday. 
Kelsey Webb had three kills, one ace, one block for the Lady Mustangs. Taylor Graham had four kills, two blocks. Destiny Boston had three kills and one block.
